connections.
Their
lodgings
were
not
long
a
secret,
and
at
length
they
began
to
know
the
officers
themselves.
Mr.
Phillips
visited
them
all,
and
this
opened
to
his
nieces
a
store
of
felicity
unknown
before.
They
could
talk
of
nothing
but
officers;
and
Mr.
Bingley's
large
fortune,
the
mention
of
which
gave
animation
to
their
mother,
was
worthless
in
their
